Job Description
Share
Responsibilities
•Be passionate about customer service with the capability of delivering amazing ‎hospitality to our guests.‎
•Assist the Restaurant Manager in the day to day running of the restaurant. ‎
•Develop a marketing sales strategy for special occasions, holidays, corporate ‎events, brand promotions etc.‎
•Recommend a primary strategy/menu for standard promotions/events.‎
•Liaise with potential clients to show them how the restaurant can meet their needs. ‎This will involve talking to them on the telephone, showing them around the restaurant ‎and meeting with them to confirm all the details of their event. ‎
•Positive attitude and belief in providing all guests with a genuine and gratifying ‎customer experience. Ability to build rapport with clients and attention to detail to ‎ensure nothing is missed. ‎
•Prepare and implement SOP’s for group reservations and event management. ‎Establish policies, procedures and schedules for reservations and events at the ‎restaurant. ‎
•Responsible to book events, group reservations for the restaurant and capture future ‎bookings. ‎
•Organise events in an immaculate manner to ensure that everything goes smoothly ‎on the day. ‎
•In-depth knowledge of social media – facebook, twitter
•Liaise with the Kitchen, Operations, Finance and Purchasing department for group ‎event food & beverage requirements, special materials and budget costs. Meet with ‎the operations and kitchen team on floor requirements and menu requirements ‎respectively with regard to the special events, festival events, parties and related ‎requests for the event management. ‎
•Eager to spot opportunities, up-sell to offer additional products or services and go ‎the extra mile to make the client's event a true success.‎
•Participate in restaurant’s promotional activities.‎
•Deal with guest comments in a positive manner and take appropriate follow up ‎action. Communicate the complaint handling procedure and corrective action to the ‎Management.‎
•Ensure that accurate records are maintained of all events and filed in accordance ‎with the company policy and procedures. ‎
•Co-ordinate all PR activity with PR company.‎
Desired Candidate Profile
Qualifications :‎
• Minimum Bachelors Degree (in Hospitality/Event Management/PR will be preferred)‎
• ‎2-3 years of experience in a similar role‎
Languages :‎
• English – proficiency in spoken and written English
• Arabic – preferred
• Additional languages – preferred
‎Skills :‎
•Guest service skills.‎
•Marketing, generating business leads.‎
•Planning, strong organizing and execution of events
•Excellent Communication skills
•People Skills - cultural awareness and the ability to liaise with different nationalities
•Time management - Ability to coordinate self and schedule the entire team helping ‎with the event.‎
•Creativity – must be able to Think out of the Box and be resourceful.‎
